'''''Star Wars Insider'' 65''' is the sixty-fifth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[January 21]], [[2003]]. The subscriber-exclusive edition of issue 65 included the second volume of ''[[Bantha Tracks (department)|Bantha Tracks]]'', the [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|''Star Wars'' Fan Club]] newsletter. This issue also came packaged with a fold-out map of the ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxy]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*From the Editor's Desk
*[[Star News]]: From the Worlds of Lucasfilm {{C|by [[Benjamin Harper]]}}
*[[The Jawa Trader]]
*[[Behind the Magic]] &mdash; Lesser is More {{C|by [[Rob Coleman]]}}
*[[HoloNet News (Insider)|HoloNet News]]
**[[CIS Shadowfeed Dispatch 14:2:14 Edition]]
**[[Republic HoloNet News Core Edition 14:2:12]]
*[[Gamescape]] &mdash; ''Star Wars'' Galaxies Update {{C|by [[W. Haden Blackman]]}}
*[[Bookshelf]] &mdash; Finally, Two There Are {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*[[Comics Link]] &mdash; Boba Fett's Sacrifice {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*[[Set Piece]]: The Outlander Club {{C|by [[Chris Trevas]]}}
*[[Scouting the Galaxy]] &mdash; Become 100,000 Baht Richer {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*[[Crossword (department)|Crossword]] &mdash; Who Dooku Live? {{C|by [[Michael Selinker]]}}
*[[Star Wars Q&A|''Star Wars'' Q&A]] {{C|by Pablo Hidalgo}}
*[[The Last Page]]

===Features===
*"[[Prequel Update]]" {{C|by [[Dave Gross]]}}
*:<small>It's the calm before the storm, but [[Rick McCallum]] gives us a few hints about starting production on [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|Episode III]].</small>
*"[[Inside Attack of the Clones|Inside ''Attack of the Clones'']]" {{C|by [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]]}}
*:<small>For centuries, the abandoned [[Dacho]] factory in one of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant's]] Dead Sectors has been the final resting place of millions of unfortunate workers. More recently, the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lords]] have moved in and made themselves right at home.</small>
*"[[Meet the Makers: LucasArts Tells Us How It's Done]]" {{C|by [[Justin Lambros]]}}
*:<small>Peer behind the digital curtain and see how a video game goes from concept to cashier.</small>
*"[[Red Five, I'm Going In: The History of Star Wars Video Games|Red Five, I'm Going In: The History of ''Star Wars'' Video Games]]" {{C|by [[David Maddox]]}}
*:<small>For twenty years, ''Star Wars'' fans have relived the excitement of the movies through video games. Take a walk down memory lane, and look ahead to the future of ''Star Wars'' gaming.</small>
*"[[Who's Who in Star Wars Galaxies|Who's Who in ''Star Wars'' Galaxies]]" {{C|by [[J.D. Wiker|JD Wiker]]}}
*:<small>[[LucasArts]] Entertainment Company and [[Sony]] Online Entertainment introduce twenty characters you can meet, greet and (probably not) defeat in its massively multiplayer online roleplaying game.</small>
*"[[The Pengalan Tradeoff]]" {{C|by [[Aaron Allston]]}}
*:<small>[[Joram Kithe]] is a [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] accountant who's dodged responsibility his entire life. Somehow, he's ended up stranded on the battlefield in charge of a [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone trooper]] platoon.</small>
*"[[Making the Map]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>If you enjoyed poring over the map included in this issue of ''Star Wars Insider'', you'll find its evolution from simple ink drawing to lavish illustration equally compelling.</small>
*"[[Jedi Knights & Vampire Slayers]]" {{C|by Dave Gross}}
*:<small>''Buffy the Vampire Slayer'' is full of pop-culture references, especially those of the writers' favorite space fantasy.</small>
*"[[Insider Interview]]: Dexter Jettster" {{C|by [[Kevin Rubio]]}}
*:<small>''Star Wars Insider'' sent Kevin Rubio to the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Galactic Core]] to interview some of the galaxy's movers and shakers. Always thinking with his stomach, Kevin made lunch his first priority.</small>

